data.name: pictureBox11.ToolTip
data.value:
Most CBZ-Readers ignore the ComicInfo.xml Page-Index and rely on filename ordering instead. If enabled, any renaming options are ignored and the files are automatically renamed according to their index. The page with type 'FrontCover' should be at index 1.
Note: If writing XML-Pageindex is set to FALSE, this option will be forced and cannot be disabled!

data.name: pictureBox16.ToolTip
data.value: By default the CBZ- Standard does not allow for files being located within any subfolders in the archive! Disabling this, will try to load all files from the Archive. It is NOT recommendet to use this option. as it can lead to inconsistent files when saving this type of Archive again! (Default=True)

data.name: pictureBox13.ToolTip
data.value:
List of filenames, that will be ignored/skipped when adding new files or folders. Only enter filenames without path. To filter for an exact name you can include the file-extension i.e. image.JPG.
To filter specific filename with ANY extension, omit it completely.

data.name: pictureBox3.ToolTip
data.value: By default, when opening a cbz-archive, all files and info from the ComicInfo.xml -Pageindex is verified with actual image data. By enabling this, opening archives will be significatly faster. (Default = False)

data.name: pictureBox2.ToolTip
data.value:
Specifies the MetaData -Format that is written to the archive. Where:
VERSION_1 = <Image="[Page #]" Key="[FileName]" ... >
VERSION_2 = <Image="[FileName]" Key="[UniqueID]" ...>
(VERSION_1 is the current comicinfo.xml specification)
